            <summary class="font-label font-bold text-on-surface cursor-pointer">How do I prevent mold and odors in used boxes in humid climates?</summary>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm mt-3 leading-relaxed">Use silica gel packets or desiccant bags inside boxes. Store in well-ventilated areas, not sealed attics. Add cedar blocks or neem powder for natural odor and pest control.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="group border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-4">
            <summary class="font-label font-bold text-on-surface cursor-pointer">Where's the best place to store seasonal boxes at home?</summary>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm mt-3 leading-relaxed">Cool, dry spots: under-bed storage, closet shelves, or spare rooms. Avoid direct sunlight, basements (flooding risk), and areas prone to temperature fluctuations. Elevated shelving protects from floor moisture.</p>
          </details>

